<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-08-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-08-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="298" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d298">
                            <head><seg type="margin">[767]</seg> *<hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Davis</persName>, Acting Secretary of State, to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Barlow</persName>, United States
                                    marshal.</hi></head>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                        State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-08-13"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 13,
                                1869</date>.</dateline>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I give you herewith, for your
                                information, a transcript of a letter from the Acting Secretary of
                                the Navy, of the 11th instant, relative to the transfer of the
                                Spanish gun-boats which were recently seized by order of the
                                President, to the custody of the commandant of the navy-yard at New
                                York.</p>
                            <p>I have the honor to be, &amp;c.,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>J. C. B. DAVIS,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting
                                    Secretary.</hi></signed>
                            </closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Francis C. Barlow</hi>, Esq.,<lb/><hi rend="italic">United States Marshal, New York.</hi></p>
                            </postscript>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>